name: globals
description: Documentation for the various things Figura adds to the global lua state.

methods.name: log
methods.description: An alias for print().

methods.name: print
methods.description: A function that writes its arguments to chat. Even though the syntax says only one argument, you can put as many as you want. All of them will print, and they'll be separated by some spaces.

methods.name: require
methods.description: The require() function takes the name of one of your scripts, without the .lua extension. If this script has not been already run before, it will run that script and return the value that script returns. If it has been run before, then it will not run the file again, but it will return the same thing as the first time. If a required script has no returns, then require() will return true. If the name you give isn't any of your scripts, it will error.

methods.name: printJson
methods.description: Takes a Minecraft json string as an argument, and prints it to the chat formatted.

methods.name: logJson
methods.description: An alias for printJson().

methods.name: printTable
methods.description: The first argument is either a Table, or it's a Userdata, which refers to any of the added Figura types. Prints the table out to chat, specially formatted. If userdata is passed in, it is automatically converted to a table or string, and displayed. In the case of tables inside of tables, the "maxDepth" parameter will be used to determine how far to go. BE CAREFUL WITH RECURSIVE TABLES! If you try to print a table too deeply, then your game may freeze while it calculates everything to print, and you may have to restart your client if you go too crazy with it. Default value for maxDepth is 1.

methods.name: logTable
methods.description: An alias for printTable().

action_wheel.name: ActionWheelAPI
action_wheel.description: A global API which is used for customizing your player's Action Wheel.

methods.name: execute
methods.description: Executes the action of the given index. If the index is null, it will execute the last selected action. A second parameter can be given to specify if it should be executed the left or right action.

methods.name: isEnabled
methods.description: Returns if the Action Wheel is being currently rendered or not.

methods.name: createPage
methods.description: Creates a new Page for the action wheel. A Title can be given to store this page internally. If no Title is given, the Page will just be returned from this function.

methods.name: getSelected
methods.description: Returns the index of the currently selected action.

methods.name: setPage
methods.description: Sets the Page of the action wheel to the given Title or Page.

methods.name: getPage
methods.description: Returns an stored Page by the given title.

action_wheel.name: Page
action_wheel.description: An Action Wheel container which is used to store up to 8 actions.

methods.name: newAction
methods.description: Adds a new Click Action on the selected Page's index. If no index is given it is added in the first available index.

methods.name: newToggle
methods.description: Adds a new Toggle Action on the selected Page's index. If no index is given it is added in the first available index.

methods.name: getAction
methods.description: Gets an Action from the Page's given index.

methods.name: newScroll
methods.description: Adds a new Scroll Action on the selected Page's index. If no index is given it is added in the first available index.

world.name: WorldAPI
world.description: A global API dedicated to reading information from the Minecraft world. Accessed using the name "world".

methods.name: exists
methods.description: Checks whether or not a world currently exists. This will almost always be true, but might be false on some occasions such as while travelling between dimensions.

methods.name: getTime
methods.description: Gets the current game time of the world. If delta is passed in, then it adds delta to the time. The default value of delta is zero.

methods.name: getTimeOfDay
methods.description: Gets the current day time of the world. If delta is passed in, then it adds delta to the time. The default value of delta is zero.

methods.name: getStrongRedstonePower
methods.description: Gets the direct redstone power level of the block at the given position.

methods.name: getBiome
methods.description: Gets the Biome located at the given position.

methods.name: getBlockState
methods.description: Gets the BlockState of the block at the given position.

methods.name: getRedstonePower
methods.description: Gets the redstone power level of the block at the given position.

methods.name: getMoonPhase
methods.description: Gets the current moon phase of the world, stored as an integer.

methods.name: getPlayers
methods.description: Returns a table containing instances of Player for all players in the world. The players are indexed by their names.

methods.name: getSkyLightLevel
methods.description: Gets the sky light level of the block at the given position.

methods.name: getLightLevel
methods.description: Gets the overall light level of the block at the given position.

methods.name: isThundering
methods.description: Gets whether or not there is currently thunder/lightning happening in the world.

methods.name: getRainGradient
methods.description: Gets the current rain gradient in the world, interpolated from the previous tick to the current one. The default value of delta is 1, which is the current tick.

methods.name: getBlockLightLevel
methods.description: Gets the block light level of the block at the given position.

methods.name: isOpenSky
methods.description: Gets whether or not the sky is open at the given position.

world.name: BlockState
world.description: A proxy for a block state from Minecraft. Instances are obtained through the WorldAPI. This proxy also contains a saved position for the BlockState.

methods.name: isOpaque
methods.description: Gets whether or not this BlockState is opaque.

methods.name: exists
methods.description: Checks whether or not this BlockState currently exists. I can't think of a situation where it wouldn't exist, but this function is provided for you to check just in case.

methods.name: getVelocityMultiplier
methods.description: Gets the velocity multiplier of this BlockState. (Only Soul sand, honey blocks in vanilla)

methods.name: getJumpVelocityMultiplier
methods.description: Gets the jump velocity multiplier of this BlockState. (Literally just honey blocks in vanilla)

methods.name: hasCollision
methods.description: Returns true if this block has collision.

methods.name: getComparatorOutput
methods.description: Gets the amount of signal strength a comparator would get from this BlockState.

methods.name: hasEmissiveLighting
methods.description: Gets whether or not the BlockState uses emissive lighting.

methods.name: getHardness
methods.description: Gets the hardness of the BlockState.

methods.name: getMaterial
methods.description: Gets the name of the material this block is made of.

methods.name: getLuminance
methods.description: Gets the emission light level of this BlockState.

methods.name: getPos
methods.description: Returns the saved position for this BlockState proxy. The saved position is used in BlockState functions that require a position.

methods.name: setPos
methods.description: Sets the saved position for this BlockState proxy. The saved position is used in BlockState functions that require a position.

methods.name: hasBlockEntity
methods.description: Gets whether or not this BlockState has an associated block entity.

methods.name: getOutlineShape
methods.description: Returns a table representing the bounding boxes of the outline shape. The table a list of Vector6, where the first 3 coordinates are one corner of the box and the last 3 are the other corner.

methods.name: isFullCube
methods.description: Gets whether or not the BlockState has a full cube as its collision hitbox.

methods.name: getOpacity
methods.description: Gets the opacity of the BlockState, in terms of how much it affects light levels.

methods.name: emitsRedstonePower
methods.description: Gets whether or not this BlockState emits redstone power.

methods.name: getFriction
methods.description: Gets the friction of this BlockState. (Slime blocks and ice in vanilla)

methods.name: getBlastResistance
methods.description: Gets the blast resistance of this BlockState.

methods.name: isTranslucent
methods.description: Gets whether or not the BlockState would propagate sky light downwards.

methods.name: getTags
methods.description: Returns a table containing all the tags of this block, as strings.

methods.name: isSolidBlock
methods.description: Gets whether or not the BlockState is considered a "solid" block by Minecraft.

methods.name: getMapColor
methods.description: Gets the map color of this BlockState, as a Vector3 with R,G,B ranging 0 to 1.

methods.name: asItem
methods.description: Returns an ItemStack representing this block in item form, whatever Minecraft deems that to be. If it cannot find an item for this block, it will return nil.

methods.name: getSounds
methods.description: Gets the names of all the sounds which can play from this BlockState, as well as their pitch and volume. Stored in a table.

methods.name: getCollisionShape
methods.description: Returns a table representing the bounding boxes of the collision shape. The table a list of Vector6, where the first 3 coordinates are one corner of the box and the last 3 are the other corner.

methods.name: getEntityData
methods.description: Returns the nbt of the Block Entity associated with this BlockState, at its position, as a table. Since the mod is only on client side, this NBT might not actually contain the real nbt, which is stored server-side.

methods.name: toStateString
methods.description: Converts this BlockState into a string, like you'd see in a Minecraft command.

methods.name: getFluidTags
methods.description: Returns a table containing all the fluid tags of this block, as strings.

fields.name: id
fields.description: The identifier of the block this BlockState comes from.

fields.name: properties
fields.description: A table containing the properties of this BlockState. If this BlockState has no properties, it is nil.

world.name: ItemStack
world.description: A proxy for an item stack from Minecraft.

methods.name: getName
methods.description: Gets the name of the item.

methods.name: exists
methods.description: Checks whether or not this ItemStack currently exists. Minecraft may delete ItemStack instances on occasion. I don't think it will delete them while they're in someone's inventory or on the ground, but testing is required to know for sure. Contact devs once someone has an answer to when these stop existing!

methods.name: getCount
methods.description: Gets the number of items in this stack.

methods.name: getTags
methods.description: Gets all the tags of this item as strings in a table.

methods.name: getDamage
methods.description: Gets the damage value of the item in this stack. Works on things like tools, or other things with a durability bar.

methods.name: getUseAction
methods.description: Returns the name of the animation that plays when using this item.

methods.name: getCooldown
methods.description: Gets the remaining cooldown on this item, in ticks.

methods.name: hasGlint
methods.description: Returns true if this item glows with enchantment glint.

methods.name: isBlockItem
methods.description: Returns true if this item represents a block.

methods.name: isFood
methods.description: Returns true if this item is edible.

methods.name: getMaxCount
methods.description: Gets the maximum stack size of this item.

methods.name: isEnchantable
methods.description: Returns true if this item stack can be put in an enchanting table.

methods.name: isDamageable
methods.description: Returns true if this item stack has durability.

methods.name: getRarity
methods.description: Gets the rarity of this item stack. COMMON = white, UNCOMMON = yellow, RARE = aqua, EPIC = light purple.

methods.name: getUseDuration
methods.description: Gets the number of ticks needed to "use" this item. Currently only has a use for food items. Always 32 for food items except kelp, which is 16.

methods.name: toStackString
methods.description: Converts this ItemStack to a string, like you'd see in a command.

methods.name: isStackable
methods.description: Returns true if the item is stackable.

methods.name: getRepairCost
methods.description: Gets the repair cost modifier, in an anvil, for this item stack.

methods.name: getMaxDamage
methods.description: Gets the maximum durability of this item stack.

fields.name: id
fields.description: Contains the id of the item this ItemStack refers to.

fields.name: tag
fields.description: A table containing the NBT tag of this ItemStack. If this ItemStack has nothing in its tag, it is nil.

world.name: Biome
world.description: A proxy for a Minecraft biome. Instances are obtained through the WorldAPI. This proxy also contains a saved position for the Biome.

methods.name: exists
methods.description: Checks whether or not this Biome currently exists. I can't think of a situation where it wouldn't exist, but this function is provided for you to check just in case.

methods.name: getPos
methods.description: Returns the saved position for this Biome's proxy. The saved position is used in Biome functions that require a position.

methods.name: setPos
methods.description: Sets the saved position for this Biome's proxy. The saved position is used in Biome functions that require a position.

methods.name: getTemperature
methods.description: Gets the temperature of this biome.

methods.name: getPrecipitation
methods.description: Gets the rain type of this biome. The type can be "NONE", "RAIN" or "SNOW".

methods.name: getFoliageColor
methods.description: Gets this biome's foliage color as a RGB vector.

methods.name: getSkyColor
methods.description: Gets this biome's sky color as a RGB vector.

methods.name: getGrassColor
methods.description: Gets this biome's grass color as a RGB vector.

methods.name: isHot
methods.description: Checks if this biome is hot.

methods.name: getWaterFogColor
methods.description: Gets this biome's water fog color as a RGB vector.

methods.name: getWaterColor
methods.description: Gets this biome's water color as a RGB vector.

methods.name: isCold
methods.description: Checks if this biome is cold.

methods.name: getDownfall
methods.description: Gets this biome's humidity.

methods.name: getFogColor
methods.description: Gets this biome's fog color as a RGB vector.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the biome, according to the registry.

keybind.name: KeybindAPI
keybind.description: A global API containing a function to create new Keybind instances.

methods.name: create
methods.description: Creates and returns a new Keybind. The name is used in the keybind menu. The key parameter is an identifier for a key, such as "key.keyboard.r". The boolean gui indicates whether the keybind should always work, or if it should only work when you don't have a screen open. Check the docs list command for all key names.

methods.name: getVanillaKey
methods.description: Gets the id of the key bound to the given action, as a string. Check the docs list command for all key names and vanilla actions.

keybind.name: Keybind
keybind.description: Represents a key binding for your script. Instances are obtained using the KeybindAPI's create() function.

methods.name: getName
methods.description: Gets the name of the keybind, which you set when you created the keybind.

methods.name: getKey
methods.description: Gets the current key for this keybind.

methods.name: isDefault
methods.description: Checks whether this key is currently set to its default state (not been changed using the keybind menu)

methods.name: setKey
methods.description: Sets the key for this keybind.

methods.name: isPressed
methods.description: Gets whether this keybind is currently pressed down.

methods.name: getKeyName
methods.description: Gets the name of the current key for this keybind.

fields.name: onPress
fields.description: A function that runs when the key is pressed down.

fields.name: onRelease
fields.description: A function that runs when the key is released.

fields.name: enabled
fields.description: Toggles if this keybind should be processed or not.

fields.name: gui
fields.description: Whenever or not this keybind should run when a GUI is open.

fields.name: override
fields.description: Toggles if this keybind should stop vanilla keys from running.

model.name: ModelPart
model.description: Represents a node in the model tree, basically a group/cube/mesh in Blockbench. Each bbmodel file is itself a ModelPart, and all of your models are contained in a global ModelPart called "models".

methods.name: getParent
methods.description: Gets the parent part of this part. If this part has no parent, returns nil.

methods.name: getType
methods.description: Returns whether this part is a "GROUP", a "CUBE", or a "MESH".

methods.name: getChildren
methods.description: Gets the children of this part, stored in a table.

methods.name: setColor
methods.description: Sets the color multiplier for this part. Values are RGB from 0 to 1. Default values are 1, indicating white/no color change.

methods.name: setScale
methods.description: Sets the scale factor for this part. Nil values for scale are assumed to be 1.

methods.name: getTask
methods.description: Gets the Render Task with the given name from this part.

methods.name: setVisible
methods.description: Sets this part to be visible or invisible. The default value is nil, meaning the part copies its visibility from its parent part. If you want to set the visibility back to the default value of nil, use resetVisible() instead.

methods.name: getVisible
methods.description: Gets whether or not this model part is visible. The default value is nil, meaning it copies the visibility of its parent part during rendering.

methods.name: addItem
methods.description: Adds a new Item Render Task on this part.

methods.name: getColor
methods.description: Gets the color multiplier of this part. Values are RGB from 0 to 1. Default values are 1, indicating white/no color change.

methods.name: getPos
methods.description: Gets the position of the model part, as an offset from its position in blockbench. Only changes from {0,0,0} when you call setPos().

methods.name: getScale
methods.description: Gets the scale of the model part, as a multiple of its blockbench size. Only changes from {1,1,1} when you call setScale().

methods.name: setPos
methods.description: Sets the position offset for this part from its blockbench position. Nil values for position are assumed to be 0.

methods.name: getOpacity
methods.description: Gets the opacity multiplier of this part. Note that opacity settings will only take effect if the part has a suitable Render Type for them, mainly TRANSLUCENT. Check out modelPart.setPrimaryRenderType() for how to do this.

methods.name: offsetPivot
methods.description: Sets the offset pivot point for this part. Nil values are assumed to be 0. For absolute pivot point values, check out the non-offset pivot functions.

methods.name: getAnimPos
methods.description: Gets the position offset provided by the currently active animation of this model part.

methods.name: getAnimRot
methods.description: Gets the rotation offset provided by the currently active animation of this model part.

methods.name: getAnimScale
methods.description: Gets the scale multiplier provided by the currently active animation of this model part.

methods.name: offsetRot
methods.description: Sets the offset rotation for this part. Nil values for rotation are assumed to be 0. Angles are given in degrees. For absolute rotation values, check out the non-offset rot functions.

methods.name: setPivot
methods.description: Sets the absolute pivot for this part. Nil values are assumed to be 0. For relative pivot offsets, check out the "offset" pivot functions.

methods.name: resetVisible
methods.description: Resets the visibility status of the part to default. The default value is nil, meaning the part copies the visibility from its parent part.

methods.name: getPositionMatrix
methods.description: Recalculates the matrix for this model part, based on its current position, rotation, scale, and pivot, then returns this matrix.

methods.name: getNormalMatrixRaw
methods.description: Returns the normal matrix for this model part. The Raw version of the function is different in that it doesn't recalculate the matrix before returning it.

methods.name: getNormalMatrix
methods.description: Recalculates the normal matrix for this model part, based on its current position, rotation, scale, and pivot, then returns this matrix.

methods.name: getRot
methods.description: Gets the rotation of the model part, including its rotation in blockbench. For relative rotation values, check out the "offset" rot functions.

methods.name: getOffsetPivot
methods.description: Gets the offset pivot of the model part, offset from its pivot in blockbench. For absolute pivot point values, check out the non-offset pivot functions.

methods.name: getOffsetRot
methods.description: Gets the offset rotation of the model part, offset from its rotation in blockbench. For absolute rotation values, check out the non-offset rot functions.

methods.name: setRot
methods.description: Sets the absolute rotation for this part. Nil values for rotation are assumed to be 0. Angles are given in degrees. For relative rotation values, check out the "offset" rot functions.

methods.name: setMatrix
methods.description: Sets the given matrix as the position matrix for this model part. The normal matrix is automatically calculated as the inverse transpose of this matrix. Calling this DOES NOT CHANGE the values of position, rot, or scale in the model part. If you call setPos() or a similar function, the effects of setMatrix() will be overwritten.

methods.name: getPivot
methods.description: Gets the pivot point of the model part, including its pivot in blockbench. For relative values, check out the "offset" pivot functions.

methods.name: setPrimaryTexture
methods.description: Sets the primary texture override of this part. Check the TextureType types in the list docs. If using "resource", the second parameter should indicate the path to the Minecraft texture you want to use.

methods.name: getTextureSize
methods.description: Gets the width, height of this part's texture in pixels. If this part has multiple different-sized textures on it, it throws an error instead.

methods.name: setUV
methods.description: Sets the UV of this part. This function is normalized, meaning it works with values 0 to 1. If you say setUV(0.5, 0.25), for example, it will scroll by half of your texture width to the right, and one fourth of the texture width downwards.

methods.name: setUVPixels
methods.description: Sets the UV of this part in pixels. Automatically divides by the results of getTextureSize(), so you can just input the number of pixels you want the UV to scroll by. Errors if the part has multiple different-sized textures.

methods.name: setOpacity
methods.description: Sets the opacity multiplier of this part. Note that opacity settings will only take effect if the part has a suitable Render Type for them, mainly TRANSLUCENT. Check out modelPart.setPrimaryRenderType() for how to do this.

methods.name: setLight
methods.description: Sets the light level to be used when rendering this part. Values you give are 0 to 15, indicating the block light and sky light levels you want to use. Passing nil will reset the lighting override for this part.

methods.name: partToWorldMatrix
methods.description: Gets a matrix which transforms a point from this part's position to a world location. Recommended to use this in POST_RENDER, as by then the matrix is updated. In RENDER it will be 1 frame behind the part's visual position for that frame. Also, if the model is not rendered in-world, the part's matrix will not be updated. Paperdoll rendering and other UI rendering will not affect this matrix.

methods.name: setUVMatrix
methods.description: Sets the UV matrix of this part. This matrix is applied to all UV points during the transform, with the UVs treated as homogeneous vectors. setUV() and setUVPixels() are actually just simpler ways of setting this matrix.

methods.name: getLight
methods.description: Gets the light level you set earlier to this part. Does not interact with Minecraft's lighting system, only retrieving values you set earlier with setLight().

methods.name: setParentType
methods.description: Sets the parent type of the part. See the ParentType parts in the list docs for legal types.

methods.name: addBlock
methods.description: Adds a new Block Render Task on this part.

methods.name: removeTask
methods.description: Removes the Task with the given name from this part.

methods.name: getParentType
methods.description: Returns the current parent type of the part.

methods.name: addText
methods.description: Adds a new Text Render Task on this part.

methods.name: getSecondaryRenderType
methods.description: Gets the current secondary render type of this model part. Nil by default, meaning the part copies the secondary render type of its parent.

methods.name: setPrimaryRenderType
methods.description: Sets the current primary render type of this model part. Nil by default, meaning the part copies the primary render type of its parent during rendering. Check the docs list command for all render types.

methods.name: getPrimaryRenderType
methods.description: Gets the current primary render type of this model part. Nil by default, meaning the part copies the primary render type of its parent.

methods.name: setSecondaryTexture
methods.description: Sets the secondary texture override of this part. Check the TextureType types in the list docs. If using "resource", the second parameter should indicate the path to the Minecraft texture you want to use.

methods.name: getPositionMatrixRaw

fields.description: The WORLD_RENDER event is run every frame, before the world is rendered. Always runs when a world is visible, even when the avatar itself is not, so this runs even in first person. Takes a parameter delta, which is a number from 0 to 1 indicating the proportion of the way the game is between ticks.

fields.name: POST_WORLD_RENDER
fields.description: The POST_WORLD_RENDER event runs every frame, after the world is rendered. Always runs when a world is visible, even when the avatar itself is not, so this runs even in first person. Takes a parameter delta, which is a number from 0 to 1 indicating the proportion of the way the game is between ticks.

fields.name: CHAT_SEND_MESSAGE
fields.description: The CHAT_SEND_MESSAGE event is run every time you send a message in chat. A string parameter is passed in, which contains the message that was sent.

fields.name: CHAT_RECEIVE_MESSAGE
fields.description: The CHAT_RECEIVE_MESSAGE event is run every time a message is received in chat. A string parameter is passed in, which contains the message you received.

event.name: Event
event.description: A hook for a certain event in Minecraft. You may register functions to one, and those functions will be called when the event occurs.

methods.name: remove
methods.description: Removes the function specified from the event. The default index is 1, which is the first function you registered. If you provide an integer, then the function at that index is removed. If you provide a name, then all functions registered under that name are removed. Returns true if a function was removed, and false otherwise.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clears the given event of all its functions.

methods.name: register
methods.description: Registers the given function to the given event. When the event occurs, the function will be run. Functions are run in the order they were registered. The optional name parameter is used when you wish to later remove a function from the event.

methods.name: getCount
methods.description: Returns the number of functions registered to this event.

methods.name: getRot

misc.name: ClientAPI
misc.description: A global API used to interact with the current Minecraft client. Most of its functions return things that can be found in the F3 menu.

methods.name: getVersion
methods.description: Returns the "version" of your client. In testing, this returned "Fabric".

methods.name: getEntityStatistics
methods.description: Returns a string containing information about the loaded entities on the client. This string appears in the F3 menu.

methods.name: isDebugOverlayEnabled
methods.description: Returns true if the F3 screen is currently open.

methods.name: getScaledWindowSize
methods.description: Returns the size of the window in Minecraft's interal GUI units.

methods.name: getSoundStatistics
methods.description: Returns a string containing information about the currently playing sounds on the client. This string appears in the F3 menu.

methods.name: getVersionType
methods.description: Returns the "version type" of your client. In testing, this returned "Fabric".

methods.name: getFPS
methods.description: Gets the FPS of the client. Returns 0 if the fps counter isn't ready yet (or if your pc is just that bad).

methods.name: getServerBrand
methods.description: Returns the type of server you're on. In singleplayer, this is "Integrated".

methods.name: getFPSString
methods.description: Gets the FPS string of the client, displayed in the F3 menu. Contains info on the fps, the fps limit, vsync, cloud types, and biome blend radius.

methods.name: getChunkStatistics
methods.description: Returns a string containing information about the player's chunk. This string appears in the F3 menu.

methods.name: isPaused
methods.description: Returns true if the client is paused.

methods.name: getEntityCount
methods.description: Returns the number of currently loaded entities.

methods.name: getFOV
methods.description: Returns the current FOV option of the client, not including additional effects such as speed or sprinting.

methods.name: getSystemTime
methods.description: Returns the current system time in milliseconds.

methods.name: getCameraPos
methods.description: Returns the position of the viewer's camera.

methods.name: getMousePos
methods.description: Returns the position of the mouse in pixels, relative to the top-left corner.

methods.name: getAllocatedMemory
methods.description: Returns the maximum amount of memory that Minecraft can possibly use.

methods.name: isHudEnabled
methods.description: Returns true if the hud is enabled (F1 disables the HUD).

methods.name: isWindowFocused
methods.description: Returns true if the Minecraft window is currently focused.

methods.name: getGuiScale

methods.name: getCameraRot
methods.description: Returns the rotation of the viewer's camera.

methods.name: getMaxMemory
methods.description: Returns the maximum amount of memory that Minecraft will try to use.

methods.name: getWindowSize

methods.name: getUsedMemory

methods.name: getJavaVersion

misc.name: RendererAPI
misc.description: A global API providing functions that change the way Minecraft renders your player.

methods.name: isFirstPerson
methods.description: Checks if your camera is in the first person view.

methods.name: setShadowRadius
methods.description: Sets the radius of your shadow. The default value is nil, which means to use the vanilla default of 0.5 for players. The maximum value is 12.

methods.name: isCameraBackwards
methods.description: Checks if your camera is in the backwards third person view.

methods.name: setCameraRot
methods.description: Sets the absolute rotation of the camera. Nil values for rotation are assumed to be 0. For relative rotation values, check out the "offset" rot function.

methods.name: getShadowRadius
methods.description: Gets the radius of your shadow. The default value is nil, which means to use the vanilla default of 0.5 for players.

methods.name: setCameraBonusRot
methods.description: figura.docs.renderer.set_camera_bonus_rot

methods.name: setPostEffect
methods.description: Sets the current rendering effect. Same as the discontinued Super Secret Settings.

fields.name: renderFire
fields.description: Whether or not you should visually have the fire effect while on fire. True by default.

fields.name: renderVehicle
fields.description: Whether or not your vehicle (boat, minecart, horse, whatever) will be rendered. True by default.

misc.name: SoundAPI
misc.description: A global API which is used to play Minecraft sounds. Accessed using the name "sound".

methods.name: playSound
methods.description: Plays the specified sound at the specified position with the given volume and pitch multipliers. The sound id is either an identifier or the custom sound name. Volume in Minecraft refers to how far away people can hear the sound from, not the actual loudness of it. If you don't give values for volume and pitch, the default values are 1.

methods.name: stopSound
methods.description: Stops the playing sounds from this avatar. If an id is specified, it only stops the sounds from that id.

misc.name: ParticleAPI
misc.description: A global API which is used for dealing with Minecraft's particles. Can currently only be used to summon a particle. Accessed using the name "particle".

methods.name: addParticle
methods.description: Creates a particle with the given name at the specified position, with the given velocity. Some particles have special properties, like the "dust" particle. For these particles, the special properties can be put into the "name" parameter, the same way as it works for commands.

methods.name: priority
methods.description: Sets the animation's priority. Instead of blending, low priority animations are overridden by high priority ones.

methods.name: length
methods.description: Set the animation's length, in seconds.

methods.name: blend
methods.description: Sets the animation's keyframe blend factor.

methods.name: offset
methods.description: Sets how much time to skip for the animation. The time is skipped on every loop.

methods.name: stop
methods.description: Stop the animation.

methods.name: override
methods.description: Set if this animation should override its part transforms.

methods.name: loop
methods.description: Sets the animation's loop mode.

methods.name: getTime
methods.description: Get the animation's playback current time.

methods.name: setTime
methods.description: Sets the animation's playback current time.

methods.name: speed
methods.description: Sets the animation's playback speed. Negative numbers can be used for an inverted animation.

methods.name: play
methods.description: Initializes the animation. Resume the animation if it was paused.

methods.name: pause
methods.description: Pause the animation's playback.

methods.name: getPlayState
methods.description: Get the animation's playback state.

methods.name: loopDelay
methods.description: Set how much time to wait in between the loops of this animation.

methods.name: addCode
methods.description: Adds a string to run in a determinant time. If theres already code to run at that time, it is overridden.

methods.name: restart
methods.description: Restarts the animation. Plays the animation if it was stopped. This behaviour can also be reproduced by stopping then playing the animation

methods.name: startDelay
methods.description: Set how much time to wait before this animation is initialized. Note that while it is waiting, the animation is considered being played.

fields.name: name
fields.description: This animation's name.
